Reasoning: 
- cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) is the most likely category as the paper focuses on designing faster and more work-efficient parallel graph algorithms. 
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is also likely as the paper discusses the construction of spanners and hopsets, which are important data structures in graph theory. 
- cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) is another possible category as the paper involves probabilistic guarantees and analyses of the overall process. 
- cs.NA (Numerical Analysis) is a less likely category, but still possible as the paper deals with approximating shortest paths in graphs. 
- cs.GR (Computer Graphics) is unlikely as the paper does not involve any visual or graphical aspects.
